

<worksheet xml:id="A23_Partial-derivatives">
  <title>Math 150  Activity 23: Partial derivatives</title>
  <p>
    The same derivative rules we have been using apply to functions with more than one variable.
    The trick is to pay attention to which variable is to be treated as <q>the variable</q>.
    Just as there are two notations for a derivative with a single variable,
    there are two ways of writing a first derivative for functions with several variables.
  </p>

  <sidebyside>

    <exercise>
      <statement>
        <p>
          Find both partial derivatives of the indicated functions.
        </p>

        <task workspace="10%">
          <p>
            <m>f(x,y) = 2xy - 7x</m>
          </p>

          <p>
            <m>f_x =</m> <fillin characters="10"/>
          </p>

          <p>
            <m>f_y =</m> <fillin characters="10"/>
          </p>
        </task>

        <task workspace="10%">
          <p>
            <m>g(a,b) = b \cos{(5a+1)}</m>
          </p>

          <p>
            <m>\dfrac{\partial g}{\partial a} =</m> <fillin characters="10"/>
          </p>

          <p>
            <m>\dfrac{\partial g}{\partial b} =</m> <fillin characters="10"/>
          </p>
        </task>
      </statement>
    </exercise>

    <exercise>
      <statement>
        <p>
          For the second partial derivatives,
          the <m>\partial</m> operators
          are read right-to-left.
          Make notes of which partial derivative to take first
          and which to take second.
        </p>

        <task>
          <p>
            <m>\dfrac{\partial^2 f}{(\partial x)^2}</m> First:
            <fillin characters="10"/>
            Second: <fillin characters="10"/>}
          </p>
        </task>

        <task>
          <p>
            <m>\dfrac{\partial^2 f}{\partial x \partial y}</m> First:
            <fillin characters="10"/>
            Second: <fillin characters="10"/>}
          </p>
        </task>

        <task>
          <p>
            <m>\dfrac{\partial^2 f}{\partial y \partial x}</m> First:
            <fillin characters="10"/>
            Second: <fillin characters="10"/>}
          </p>
        </task>

        <task>
          <p>
            <m>\dfrac{\partial^2 f}{(\partial y)^2}</m> First:
            <fillin characters="10"/>
            Second: <fillin characters="10"/>}
          </p>
        </task>
      </statement>
    </exercise>

    <exercise>
      <statement>
        <p>
          Find the partial derivatives of <m>f(t,w) = 3t^2 - tw^3 + 10</m>.
        </p>

        <task workspace="10%">
          <p>
            <m>\dfrac{\partial^2 f}{(\partial t)^2}</m>
          </p>
        </task>

        <task workspace="10%">
          <p>
            <m>\dfrac{\partial^2 f}{\partial t \partial w}</m>
          </p>
        </task>

        <task workspace="10%">
          <p>
            <m>\dfrac{\partial^2 f}{\partial w \partial t}</m>
          </p>
        </task>

        <task workspace="10%">
          <p>
            <m>\dfrac{\partial^2 f}{(\partial w)^2}</m>
          </p>
        </task>
      </statement>
    </exercise>

  </sidebyside>
</worksheet>

